  "body": "This is to provide further changes to code changes introduced by #4933 after test cases have been chaneged - ethereum\\tests for EIP-3860:\r\n\r\n- stEIP3860.create2InitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860\r\n- stEIP3860.createInitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860\r\n\r\nRoot cause is:\r\n- gas cost of CREATE/CREATE2 operations when init code size is exceeded, #4933 charged full cost - this is now changed to deduct only call charges, but without additional word cost (introduced by 3860)\r\n- #4933 changed to increment nonce when intruction ended due to init code limit exceeded - this will be \r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n - Run stEIP3860.create2InitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860 test\r\n - Run stEIP3860.createInitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860 test\r\n\r\nExpected behavior\r\n - CREATE/CREATE2 call cost shall be deducted as before 3860 (without new per word charge) when 3860 init code size limit is exceeded\r\n - nonce should NOT be incremented when 3860 init code size limit is exceeded",
